        "title": "docs: prepare ClawHub docs for Mintlify",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Converts `docs/` into the ClawHub Mintlify source tree with `docs/docs.json`, ClawHub branding, navbar, and `docs/index.md` as the home page.\n- Removes the temporary OpenClaw docs-builder bridge, sync workflow dispatch, and generated-docs preview scripts.\n- Adds a build guard so stale ignored `public/docs` output cannot be accidentally included in the app build.\n- Keeps ClawHub app/email/CLI user-facing docs links on the current `https://docs.openclaw.ai/clawhub/` host until the Mintlify `/docs` route is actually configured.\n\n## Proof\n\n- `bun run docs:check` -> passed (`success build validation passed`).\n- `bunx vitest run src/__tests__/header.test.tsx src/__tests__/ui-design-contract.test.ts src/__tests__/skills-publish-route.test.tsx src/__tests__/plugins-publish-route.test.tsx src/__tests__/package-detail-route.test.tsx convex/packageInspectorNode.test.ts convex/lib/emails.test.ts convex/packages.public.test.ts packages/schema/src/schemas.test.ts` -> 9 files / 323 tests passed.\n- `bun run --cwd packages/clawhub test:src -- src/cli/commands/packages.test.ts` -> 1 file / 66 tests passed.\n- `bun run ci:static` -> passed.\n- `VITE_CONVEX_URL=https://example.invalid bun run build` -> passed.\n- Local Mintlify preview rendered the Quickstart page with title `Quickstart - ClawHub`, ClawHub logo, search, and the ClawHub navbar link.\n\n## Review Notes\n\n- I intentionally did not switch production/user-facing links to `https://clawhub.ai/docs` in this PR. Live route probing showed `clawhub.ai/docs` currently returns 404, while `docs.openclaw.ai/clawhub` is still live.\n- Remaining cutover work: connect/configure the Mintlify project for the repo `docs/` directory, configure host-level routing for `https://clawhub.ai/docs`, then switch app/email/CLI docs links to the canonical ClawHub docs URL.\n- Ask Molty is not restored by this Mintlify-source PR; that needs a separate Mintlify-compatible assistant/auth decision before claiming the original Molty sign-in proof goal.\n- Autoreview found and we accepted one earlier P1 about switching links before `/docs` routing existed; this revision fixes that by keeping public links on the current docs host. The final rerun of the nested autoreview process hung after independently rerunning `docs:check`, app build, live route probes, and route/config inspection, so I interrupted the stuck review process and relied on the explicit verification above.\n",
